WEBVTT

00:04:57.513 --> 00:05:00.736
And so what happens is,
people just see fact, fact, fact, fact.

00:05:00.760 --> 00:05:03.101
They're all dramatic
and interesting and amazing,

00:05:03.125 --> 00:05:06.061
but collectively, somehow,
give us the wrong impression.

00:05:06.085 --> 00:05:07.260
SP: That's right.

00:05:07.284 --> 00:05:10.358
I think that's inherent
to the nature of journalism.

00:05:10.712 --> 00:05:13.365
But it is exacerbated by some habits

00:05:13.389 --> 00:05:16.172
that have become
part of journalistic culture,

00:05:16.196 --> 00:05:19.637
that I think can be separated
from the necessary fact

00:05:19.661 --> 00:05:21.747
that the news comes in every day.

00:05:22.684 --> 00:05:27.050
There is, in many universities --
and especially in humanities departments,

00:05:27.074 --> 00:05:30.147
and journalists tend to be
graduates of humanities departments --